    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i drive it i keep hearing this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. not sure if i messed up or if it's a sensor or a stuck caliper. what do u think?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That high-pitched squealing noise after brake pad replacement can be tricky to diagnose! It might simply be that the new pads need a little bed-in time to quiet down, which is common. Alternatively, it could be due to light rust on the rotors, or perhaps the pads aren't seated perfectly against the rotor surface. It's best to have a mechanic check the caliper alignment and rotor condition to be sure.",
      "source": "target",
