    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i checked the clips and they seem fine, everything looks tight. but man that sound is just so weird and piercing. it's almost like it's coming from deep inside the wheel assembly, like something is rubbing or screeching way more than it should. do you think it could be a stuck caliper piston or something causing it to rub unevenly?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A piercing sound coming from deep inside the wheel assembly while braking is definitely concerning and warrants a closer look. A stuck caliper piston or uneven pad wear can certainly cause erratic rubbing and screeching noises. Since you've confirmed the clips are tight, have a professional inspect the caliper slide pins to ensure they are moving freely. If the piston is sticking, it can cause uneven pad contact, leading to that high-pitched noise.",
      "source": "target",
